From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Codex <codex@example.com>
Date: Tue, 23 Jun 2026 00:00:00 -0700
Subject: [PATCH] Add PicoMite ARRAY SET command

PicoMite/WebMite programs use ARRAY SET value,array() to initialise an
entire array. MMB4L did not register an ARRAY command, so those programs
failed during token execution with "Unknown command".

Add the ARRAY command with the SET subcommand for integer, floating-point,
and string arrays. The implementation accepts the whole-array form only and
fills every declared element across all dimensions.
---
 CMakeLists.txt               |  1 +
 src/commands/cmd_array.c     | 103 +++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
 src/core/commandtbl.c        |  1 +
 src/core/commandtbl.h        |  1 +
 4 files changed, 106 insertions(+)
 create mode 100644 src/commands/cmd_array.c

diff --git a/CMakeLists.txt b/CMakeLists.txt
index 1111111..2222222 100644
--- a/CMakeLists.txt
+++ b/CMakeLists.txt
@@ -51,6 +51,7 @@ set(MMB4L_CORE_SOURCE_FILES
 
 set(MMB4L_COMMANDS_SOURCE_FILES
     src/commands/cmd_autosave.c
+    src/commands/cmd_array.c
     src/commands/cmd_arc.c
     src/commands/cmd_blit.c
     src/commands/cmd_box.c
diff --git a/src/commands/cmd_array.c b/src/commands/cmd_array.c
new file mode 100644
index 0000000..1111111
--- /dev/null
+++ b/src/commands/cmd_array.c
@@ -0,0 +1,103 @@
